cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this software, please cite it as below."
title: "AERIS: A Defensive Red-Teaming Framework for Large Language Models"
abstract: >-
  AERIS is a reproducible benchmark and defense suite for measuring how
  reliably a large language model resists adversarial inputs — prompt
  injection, jailbreaks, harmful-content elicitation, and indirect attacks
  via tool use. It is purely defensive: it ships only published attack
  templates as surrogate triggers, and is designed not to produce usable
  harm artifacts.
